messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /{path}

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD acceptable: false

- POST acceptable: false

- OPTIONS acceptable: true

- TRACE acceptable: false

- GET acceptable: false

- PUT acceptable: false

- DELETE acceptable: false

Explanation:
- The method is annotated with @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.OPTIONS, value = "/*"). The Ant-style pattern "/*" is a single-segment wildcard under the application root; in OpenAPI path form this is represented as a path parameter, e.g. /{path}.
- The mapping explicitly restricts the HTTP method to RequestMethod.OPTIONS, so only OPTIONS requests are handled by this controller method. There is no mapping that declares "all methods" (i.e., a @RequestMapping without a method element), so "all methods acceptable" is false.
- Because only OPTIONS is declared for this handler, no other HTTP verbs (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE, HEAD) are acceptable for this mapping according to the code. (HEAD is not declared explicitly in the code, so it is considered not acceptable per the instruction to base answers on the code, not on framework behaviors.)
